  "time_ut": 1661866154,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The budget cannot be implemented",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "National People's Shakti Member of Parliament Harini Amarasuriya said that the interim budget cannot be implemented without a stable government.",
        "The government has now reversed the decisions taken 6 months ago. A stable government is needed to implement the ideas. Much attention has been paid to education. Students from abroad have got opportunities to come and study in Sri Lanka. We will not oppose this. However, before providing facilities to foreign students, opportunities should be provided to domestic students."
      ],
